node.text:
Here's are 2 shocking facts:

39.4% of all Americans don't think their college degree was worth it. 
Wanna know why?
The fucking thing costs you at least 100k with living expenses but

28.2% of all graduates are unable to find a job within their field of study.

You could start an Amazon business 20 times over successfully for that kind of money…

And it would only take you 2-6 months instead of four years. 

I don't have an issue with college education - we need doctors and nurses but...

I got a huge problem with rip-off degrees who can't make you back your investment and indebt you for life. 

If you want such a degree, go for it. But don't pay for it with your own money.
And by God don't take on student debt for it.

Build an online business, generate the income you need and do what you want. 

If you don't know where to start, 

follow 👉 @bjkuniversity 
follow 👉 @bjkuniversity 
follow 👉 @bjkuniversity 

And they'll show you how to build an Amazon business that takes care of you and your loved ones !

Friendly reminder:

You are f*cking amazing!

Maybe you are having a rough time right now…

Maybe you are at a point where things get better…

Maybe you lost direction…

It’s all part of life.

This is your journey to success. It has ups and downs. But you’ll make it!

So, don’t be so hard on yourself.

You’ve already come so far!

Type 💪 if you agree!

And if you are ready to start a new chapter in your life…

follow 👉 @bjkuniversity

node.text:
Living for the weekends?

If you only enjoy your life 2 out of 7 days of the week…

I get you.

I used to be the same.

The weekend was the highlight of my life.

And every Monday was awful.

Well, at least until I started to work on myself.

I wanted to create a life where I can live on my own terms.

A life where I get to enjoy every day, not just the weekends.

That’s when I learned more about how wealthy people think…

And I started adopting their mindsets.

Do you want to build a life on your terms and better yourself daily?

node.text:
You are not a victim of your circumstances!

Maybe you weren't born rich and wealthy…

But that doesn’t mean you have to stay unfortunate all your life.

Maybe you admire successful sportsmen, billionaires, or public figures...

But you think you can never be like them.

Well here is a new perspective for you:

You can be anything you want if you work towards it.

Take me as an example…

I was a war refugee.

I could have sat around and complained about how unfair my life is.

But I didn’t do that.

Instead, I worked towards a life that I wanted.

Was it always easy? No it wasn’t. 

But it was well worth it...

I’m telling you this because you can do the same.

Want to get started today?

4 simple rules for life.

Learning these 4 things and implementing them in my life changed everything.

Especially when I learned to think less and act faster.

The longer you think, the more chances you have to talk yourself out of something.

But stopping yourself from overthinking isn’t always easy…

What makes it easier, though, is having supportive people around you.

If you are among other people who also work towards their goals…

They remind you to act.

You are less alone with your thoughts and everything gets easier.

node.text:
What makes you happy, motivated, and inspired?

Do you remember when you were a kid and had crazy dreams?

Maybe you wanted to be an actor, an astronaut, a billionaire…

Thinking that anything is possible makes life magical.

But as you grew older, more and more people were skeptical towards your dream.

Suddenly they told you:

Be more realistic…

Get a real job…

Nobody can make a living doing that…

It’s too hard…

So you buried your dream in the back of your head.

And did what society told you to do.

But it never got easier.

You never “learned to love” your job.

And that is a good thing. 

Because life is not about “learning to love” your job.

You already have things you love, and that’s what you should do in life.

The good news is, it’s never too late.

You can still be, do and achieve anything you want.

I believe in you.

If you want to find out how I created a life where I can do anything I want…

By starting my own Amazon business…

node.text:
There's ONE thing rich people always do but you don't:

Confidently asking for help, resources and support. 

I'm not talking about begging, or demanding free hand-outs.

I mean having a vision they are burning for …

A passion so strong that others WANT to be a part of it…

And when a passionate person, who is fully convinced their vision will come true, asks for something…

You can only say yes.

That's a quality that can make people successful.

But most people are too proud to accept help.

They think doing everything alone is a sign of strength. 

But this is complete BS. 

If this were true, no entrepreneur would need a team.

No company would need employees. 

Even Jesus had his apostles.

So don’t be so arrogant to believe you can do something new on your own without failing first. 

If you're ready to accent help in building a business and changing your life, 

follow 👉@bjkuniversity

follow 👉@bjkuniversity

Would you quit your job and travel the world?

Would you be able to afford a nice home for your family?

Would you give it to charity?

No matter what it is, a bit of extra money gives you choices and allows you to live life on your terms.

It’s not always easy. Even something seemingly simple as selling on Amazon is still a business.

It takes time and dedication…

But it’s worth it.
